  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You suddenly sprout sharp earth spikes in a 30-foot radius, impaling every creature in range. Each affected creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, they take 5d12 Earth damage and gain 1 rank of Bleeding and Bruised. On a success, they take half damage and no conditions.<br />Any downed creature in the radius has its blood drained by the jutsu, allowing you to regain 2d12 temporary HP per downed target. Additionally, for every non-downed creature that fails its saving throw, you regain 1d12 temporary HP. These temporary HP last until the start of your next turn.<br />The area becomes difficult terrain for 1 minute, though you remain unaffected by it.<br />    <strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank above B-Rank, increase the chakra cost by 3, the radius by 10 feet, and the damage by 3d12.</p>",
